Walus is serving a life sentence for the assassination of former SACP general secretary, Chris Hani, in April 1993. JOHANNESBURG - The South African Communist Party will do all in its power to ensure Janusz Walus rots in jail if he doesn't fully disclose the names of all his co-conspirators. READ: Lamola ordered to review Janusz Walus parole decision Walus is serving a life sentence for the assassination of former SACP general secretary, Chris Hani, in April 1993. In January, Walus was denied parole, but his legal team took the decision on review. On Thursday, the Pretoria High Court ordered the Justice and Correctional Services minister to review his decision not to grant Walus parole, within 60 days.